<topic id="263751ce-169e-469d-ac4a-3c1e9c574e42" revisionNumber="1">
  <developerHowToDocument xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">

    <summary>
      <para>These styles relate to the Custom <quoteInline>TargetType="{x:Type cc:DatePicker}</quoteInline>
      control class.</para>
    </summary>

    <introduction>
      <para>The control provides a dependency property to determine if error messages are shown below the control.</para>
    </introduction>

    <section>
      <title>controlDatePickerStyle</title>
      <content>
        <para>This style is automatically assigned to the Date Picker custom control:</para>
        <code language="xaml">
          <![CDATA[
<cc:DatePicker/>
]]>
        </code>
        <procedure>
          <title>Default properties</title>
          <steps class="bullet">
            <step><content><para>IsErrorShown = "False"</para></content></step>
            <step><content><para>SelectedDateFormat = "Long"</para></content></step>
          </steps>
        </procedure>
      </content>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>IsErrorShown property</title>
      <content>
        <para>Example of assigning the IsErrorShown style to a Date Picker custom control:</para>
        <code language="xaml">
          <![CDATA[
<cc:DatePicker IsErrorShown="True"/>
]]>
        </code>
        <procedure>
          <title>Notes</title>
          <steps class="ordered">
            <step><content>
              <para>Use this property to show error messages in a text block attached to the date picker.
              This allows for fields to automatically adjust their position on the form:<lineBreak/>
              <mediaLinkInline><image xlink:href="WithErrorsStyle"/></mediaLinkInline></para>
            </content></step>
            <step><content><para>To allow the whole form <legacyItalic>(i.e., Window)</legacyItalic> to
            adjust its size, the property SizeToContent="Height" must be set.</para></content></step>
          </steps>
        </procedure>
      </content>
    </section>

